
[1]interposition

   INTERPOSI'TION, n. [L. interpositio.]

   1. A being, placing or coming between; intervention; as the
   interposition of the Baltic sea between Germany and Sweden. The
   interposition of the moon between the earth and the sun occasions a
   solar eclipse.

   2. Intervenient agency; as the interposition of the magistrate in
   quieting sedition. How many evidences have we of divine interposition
   in favor of good men!

   3. Mediation; agency between parties. By the interposition of a common
   friend, the parties have been reconciled.

   4. Any thing interposed.
